    keywordsFranco: ['muscle memory', 'rag3 el gym', 'return to gym', 'regain muscle'],
    stateId: 'info_muscle_memory_science',
    response: { en: 'Muscle Memory — The Science of Coming Back: THE SCIENCE: When you build muscle, your muscle fibers gain new nuclei (myonuclei). When you stop training, muscles shrink BUT the nuclei STAY. This is permanent — they never go away. When you return to training, those nuclei rapidly rebuild the muscle. This is why someone who was muscular can regain it 2-3x faster than building it the first time. TIMELINE: After 2 weeks off: Minimal muscle loss, mostly water/glycogen. After 1 month: Some muscle loss begins, but nuclei intact. After 3-6 months: Noticeable muscle loss, but muscle memory will bring it back in 4-8 weeks of training. After 1+ year: Significant loss, but still faster recovery than starting from scratch (8-12 weeks). WHAT TO DO WHEN RETURNING: Week 1-2: 50% of previous weights, focus on form. Week 3-4: 70-80% of previous weights. Week 5-6: Back to full intensity. Don\'t rush — tendons and ligaments need more time than muscles to readapt. Injury risk is highest in first 2 weeks of returning. BEST APPROACH: Full body workouts 3x/week for first 2 weeks, then return to your normal split. Eat in slight surplus. Sleep 8+ hours. Be patient — it comes back faster than you think.', ar: 'ذاكرة العضلات — العلم: العلم: لما تبني عضلات، الألياف بتكسب نوى جديدة (ماينيوكلي). لما توقف تمرين، العضلات بتصغر بس النوى بتفضل. ده دائم — مش بتروح. لما ترجع، النوى بتبني العضلات 2-3 مرات أسرع. الجدول الزمني: أسبوعين: فقدان ضعيف. شهر: بداية فقدان. 3-6 شهور: فقدان ملحوظ بس الذاكرة بترجّعه في 4-8 أسابيع. سنة+: فقدان كبير بس أسرع من البداية. لما ترجع: أسبوع 1-2: نص الأوزان. أسبوع 3-4: 70-80%. أسبوع 5-6: شغل كامل. ما تستعجلش — الأوتار محتاجة وقت أكتر.' },
