    keywordsFranco: ['maintenance phase', 'after cut what', 'between bulk cut', 'reverse diet'],
    stateId: 'info_maintenance_phase',
    response: { en: 'Maintenance Phase — The Missing Piece of Most Diets: WHAT IS IT: A period where you eat at maintenance calories (TDEE — not gaining, not losing). Usually 2-4 weeks between bulk and cut phases. The most underrated phase in fitness. WHY IT MATTERS: Hormones normalize after dieting (leptin, thyroid, testosterone). Your body adapts to new weight (new "set point"). Mental break from restriction OR surplus. Better results when you start next phase. Performance improves. WHEN TO USE: After a cut: 2-4 weeks minimum at maintenance before bulking. After a bulk: 1-2 weeks at maintenance before cutting. After competition: 4-8 weeks at maintenance (critical for health). After any period of extreme dieting. HOW TO FIND MAINTENANCE: Take your current intake and slowly add/remove 100 cal every week until weight is stable for 2+ weeks. Or use calculator: bodyweight in kg × 33 = rough maintenance. REVERSE DIETING: After a cut, don\'t jump straight to high calories. Increase 100-200 cal per week until reaching maintenance. This prevents rapid fat regain and digestive issues. THE CYCLE: Bulk (8-16 weeks) → Maintenance (2-4 weeks) → Cut (8-12 weeks) → Maintenance (2-4 weeks) → Repeat. This is how physiques are built over years.', ar: 'مرحلة المينتننس — القطعة المفقودة: ايه هي: فترة بتاكل فيها سعرات المينتننس (مش زيادة، مش نقص). عادةً 2-4 أسابيع بين البالك والكت. ليه مهمة: الهرمونات بتتظبط. جسمك بيتأقلم على الوزن الجديد. راحة نفسية. أداء أحسن. امتى: بعد الكت: 2-4 أسابيع قبل البالك. بعد البالك: 1-2 أسبوع قبل الكت. ريفرس دايت: بعد الكت، ما تقفزش للسعرات العالية. زوّد 100-200 سعرة/أسبوع لحد المينتننس. الدورة: بالك (8-16 أسبوع) → مينتننس (2-4) → كت (8-12) → مينتننس (2-4) → كرّر.' },
