    response: { en: 'Gym Anxiety — How to Overcome It: THE TRUTH NOBODY TELLS YOU: 1) Nobody is watching you. Everyone is focused on their own workout. 2) The biggest people in the gym were once the smallest. They respect you for showing up. 3) Everyone started somewhere. LITERALLY everyone. 4) The gym is the only place where people WANT you to succeed. PRACTICAL STEPS: 1) Go during off-peak hours first (early morning, late night, 2-4 PM). 2) Have a written plan (no wandering = no awkwardness). 3) Wear headphones (universal "don\'t talk to me" signal). 4) Start with machines (guided movement, less intimidating than free weights). 5) Watch YouTube tutorials BEFORE going (know the movements). 6) Go with a friend the first few times. 7) Remember: gym membership = you have EVERY RIGHT to be there. REFRAME: That scary-looking huge guy? He\'s probably the nicest person there. Most gym regulars love helping beginners — it reminds them of their own journey. TIMELINE: Week 1-2: Nervous, awkward. Week 3-4: Starting to feel comfortable. Month 2: You have a routine. Month 3+: The gym feels like home. You\'ll wonder why you were ever scared.', ar: 'قلق الجيم — إزاي تتغلب عليه: الحقيقة اللي محدش بيقولها: 1) محدش بيبصلك. كل واحد مركّز في تمرينه. 2) أكبر واحد في الجيم كان أصغر واحد قبل كده. 3) كل الناس بدأت من الصفر. حرفياً كلهم. 4) الجيم المكان الوحيد اللي الناس عايزاك تنجح. خطوات عملية: 1) روح في أوقات فاضية الأول. 2) خد برنامج مكتوب. 3) البس سماعات. 4) ابدأ بالماشينز. 5) اتفرج يوتيوب قبل ما تروح. 6) روح مع صاحبك أول كام مرة. 7) فاكر: الاشتراك = حقك تبقى هنا. الجدول: أسبوع 1-2: متوتر. أسبوع 3-4: بتريّح. شهر 2: عندك روتين. شهر 3+: الجيم بيت تاني.' },
